----- Original Message ----- 
From: Jan Smutny-Jones 
To: Steven Kelly 
Sent: Tuesday, November 21, 2000 1:22 PM

The ISO is reporting that there is 12,000 Mws of generating currently out of 
service.  7,000 were scheduled outages.  5,000 Mws are forced outages.  The 
ISO has called 3 Stage 2 emergencies over the last several days.  The 
situation is critical.  IEP is aware that a number of its members maybe out 
on scheduled maintenance.  It would be extremely helpful if maintenance is 
expedited and units returned to service as soon as possible.
 
The IEP membership has always been helpful in meeting California's energy 
needs in time of crisis.  Historically this has involved Seismic .The events. 
The current crisis is weather driven but none the less real.  Let's keep 
those Christmas lights on.  If you are getting anything less than full 
cooperation from your local utility please advise us as soon as possible.  
Thank you for your assistance.
Jan Smutny-Jones
Executive Director
Independent Energy Producers
